<body><p>GE.13-14657 
</p>
<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-third session 
</b>Agenda item 3 
<b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Algeria*, Bolivia (Plurinational State of)*, China*, Cuba*, Ecuador, Egypt*, El 
Salvador*, Pakistan, Russian Federation*, Saudi Arabia*, Venezuela (Bolivarian 
Republic of): draft amendment 
</b></p>
<p><b>  23/&#8230;Amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/23/L.28 
</b></p>
<p> The second preambular paragraph should read 
</p>
<p> <i>Reaffirming</i> the Vienna Declaration and Programme of Action, the Declaration on 
the Elimination of Violence against Women, the Beijing Declaration and Platform for 
Action, the Programme of Action of the International Conference on Population and 
Development, and recalling Human Rights Council resolutions 7/24 of 28 March 2008, 
14/12 of 18 June 2010, 16/7 of 24 March 2011, 17/11 of 17 June 2011 and 20/12, those of 
the General Assembly and the Commission on Human Rights on the elimination of all 
forms of violence against women, and the agreed conclusions of the Commission on the 
Status of Women,1 
</p>
<p>    
</p>
<p>  
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>* Non-member State of the Human Rights Council. 
 
</p>
<p>1
  <i>Official Records of the Economic and Social Council, 2013, Supplement No. 7</i> (E/2013/27). 
</p>
